      "narrative": {
        "News": "Pemex - Deer Park: the 38,500 bpd distillate hydrotreater was shut during the evening of July 11 (EST). Decreased unit and fur- nace stack activity began at that time. Phillips 66 - Sweeny: significant elevated flaring began during the afternoon of July 11 (EST). Similar flaring has previously been as- sociated with operational issues and maintenance. Activity at all monitored units remained unchanged. Also at the refinery, the 30,000 bpd FCC was shut during the afternoon of March 28 and remained offline. Shell - Norco: the 21,380 bpd coker was shut during the morning of July 11 (EST). TotalEnergies - Port Arthur: the 165,000 bpd CDU and 55,000 bpd VDU were restarted during the evening of July 11 (EST). The 80,000 bpd FCC, 60,000 bpd coker, 10,000 bpd coker naphtha hydrotreater, 66,000 bpd ULSD hydrotreater, 39,600 bpd catalytic reformer and 45,500 bpd reformer feed hydrotreater were restarted during the morning of June 6. Increased activity began at the 80,000 bpd FCC during the morning of June 27. Increased ac- tivity began at the 60,000 bpd coker, 10,000 bpd coker naphtha hydrotreater, 66,000 bpd ULSD hydrotreater, 39,600 bpd catalytic reformer and 45,500 bpd reformer feed hydrotreater June 25. The 80,000 bpd CDU and 52,000 bpd VDU were restarted June 30. All monitored units were shut during the late evening of June 19. Marathon - El Paso: the 66,000 bpd CDU, 17,350 bpd VDU and 18,000 bpd catalytic reformer were restarted during the morning of July 12 (EST). Increased activity began at the catalytic reformer during the late evening of July 9. The 18,300 bpd gasoline hy- drotreater was restarted during the morning of July 11. The units were shut during the late evening of July 8. Valero - Corpus Christi (West): the 40,000 bpd CDU was shut during the morning of July 10 (EST).",
        "Ongoing Events": "Lazarus Energy - Nixon: the 15,000 bpd CDU was restarted dur- ing the afternoon of July 8 (EST). The unit was shut during the af- ternoon of July 6 (EST). Valero - St. Charles: the 80,000 bpd coker was shut during the evening of July 6 (EST). Decreased unit activity and excess emis- sions began at that time. Citgo - Corpus Christi: the 44,000 bpd coker was restarted dur- ing the morning of June 20. Increased activity began at the unit during the evening of June 17. The unit was shut on June 14. The 174,000 bpd CDU and 85,300 bpd VDU were shut during the late morning of June 18 and remained offline. The units were ini- tially shut on June 10. PBF - Chalmette: the 19,000 bpd catalytic reformer was shut dur- ing the afternoon of May 8. A fire was reported at the facility.",
        "Planned Maintenance": ""
      }
